<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Order_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BGarrett_Birkhoff.5D.5D1948"><a href="/wiki/Garrett_Birkhoff" title="Garrett Birkhoff">Garrett Birkhoff</a> (1948). <i>Lattice Theory, volume 25</i>. New York: Amer. Math. Soc. Coll. Publ..</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lattice+Theory%2C+volume+25&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BGarrett+Birkhoff%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BGarrett+Birkhoff%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1948&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Amer.+Math.+Soc.+Coll.+Publ.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Order_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFS._N._Burris_and_H._P._Sankappanavar1981">S. N. Burris and H. P. Sankappanavar (1981). <i><a href="http://www.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca/htdocs/ualg.html" class="external text" title="http://www.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca/htdocs/ualg.html" rel="nofollow">A Course in Universal Algebra</a></i>. Springer Verlag<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca/htdocs/ualg.html" class="external free" title="http://www.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca/htdocs/ualg.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca/htdocs/ualg.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Course+in+Universal+Algebra&amp;rft.aulast=S.+N.+Burris+and+H.+P.+Sankappanavar&amp;rft.au=S.+N.+Burris+and+H.+P.+Sankappanavar&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.pub=Springer+Verlag&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thoralf.uwaterloo.ca%2Fhtdocs%2Fualg.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Order_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>A free online introduction to universal algebra, with much material on lattices.</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFB._A._Davey_and_H._A._Priestley2002">B. A. Davey and H. A. Priestley (2002). <i>Introduction to Lattices and Order</i> (2nd ed. ed.). Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521784514" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-78451-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introduction+to+Lattices+and+Order&amp;rft.aulast=B.+A.+Davey+and+H.+A.+Priestley&amp;rft.au=B.+A.+Davey+and+H.+A.+Priestley&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.edition=2nd+ed.&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-78451-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Order_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>A good contemporary introduction to the subject. Suitable for undergraduates.</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li>G. Gierz, K. H. Hofmann, K. Keimel, J. D. Lawson, M. Mislove, and D. S. Scott (2003). "Continuous Lattices and Domains," in <i>Encyclopedia of Mathematics and its Applications</i>, Vol. 93, Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521803381" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-80338-1</a></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>The comprehensive new version of the famous "Compendium" of continuous lattices. Assumes some advanced mathematical background.</dd>
</dl>
